question
An array containing names is given. Get an array of the first letters of the names contained in the original array.
Write a function arrayOfFirstLetters that takes an array of strings names as an argument and returns an array containing 
the first letters of the strings in the original array.
Example:
arrayOfFirstLetters (["Alice", "Bob"]) should return ["A", "B"];
arrayOfFirstLetters (["Kate"]) should return ["K"];
arrayOfFirstLetters ([]) should return [].

solution:

function arrayOfFirstLetters(names){
  let newarr = [];
    for(let i = 0; i < names.length; i++){
     newarr.push(names[i][0]);
     }
     return newarr;
}
